took exception to my description of Robinson=E2=80=99s Artnet magazine as s=
parsely trafficked, and went on to assert that it was =E2=80=9Ca go-to sour=
ce for art
reviews among people who care(d) about those sorts of things. And the NYT d=
oes plenty of obits for less =E2=80=98prominent individuals.=E2=80=99=E2=80=
=9D

=C2=A0

Fair enough. I meant no disrespect to Robinson or his memory. But Artnet=E2=
=80=99s audience under Robinson was a fraction of its current footprint. (B=
y the way, the big showdown over Artnet=E2=80=99s leadership takes place on=
 Thursday. More on that in a subsequent newsletter.)
Anyway, the Times rectified the Bochner situation late last week with an ob=
ituary ( https://www.nytimes.com/2025/02/21/arts/mel-bochner-dead.html?sear=
chResultPosition=3D1&utm_campaign=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F25%2F25=
