With that in mind, Christie=E2=80=99s is likely to estimate the work
close to the record price. They=E2=80=99ll be setting a bar, and we=E2=80=
=99ll be watching to see whether that rarefied world of a few dozen collect=
ors thinks it=E2=80=99s a reasonable price=E2=80=94or even cheap. Adding to=
 the appeal of the Riggios=E2=80=99 Mondrian is the fact that the painting =
seems to be in very good condition=E2=80=94often an issue for Mondrian=E2=
=80=99s work a century after he made it.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>Clo=
se behind the Mondrian is one of the Magrittes that the Riggios acquired on=
ly in 2023. A small version of<em>
L=E2=80=99empire des lumi=C3=A8res</em>, from 1949, this painting had been =
sold in 2017 for $20.5 million. It returned to auction amid the run-up in M=
agritte prices, and contributed to steep acceleration in prices for this pa=
rticular series when the Riggios bought it for nearly $35 million.</p></div=
