ecoration:underline;color:#d40000;">obituary</a> written by <strong>Penelop=
e Green</strong> that gives the artist credit for mounting one of the first=
 conceptual art shows while teaching at SVA in the 1960s. As Green explaine=
d, Bochner believed conceptual work had to take some material form. Eventua=
lly, for
Bochner, that material form would be language.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;marg=
in-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Anyway, =
I=E2=80=99m glad the <em>Times</em> got it together. The news organization =
can be a bit of a bully in demanding to receive first crack at all major ar=
t-related announcements. That=E2=80=99s fine. It has a big audience. But if=
 its editors are going to seek to dominate a category, they also have a res=
ponsibility to cover all aspects of that world in a timely and
authoritative way, which includes having obituaries of important artists pr=
e-written. Just saying=E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"=
>=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">More tomorrow for the I=
nner Circle subscribers. See you then,</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-botto=
